window.userReviewsJSON = [{"asin":"B002V1AA7Y","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> I hate writing reviews, so when I do make an effort it's because I really enjoyed myself. I don't like putting spoiler stuff in that might ruin it for other folks and thought I had done a decent job tapping one out and then I had a phone call, had to look some up and along the way lost the text box and that review. <br><br>So here's this<br><br>Jeff is a middle aged married guy stuck in a rut working in radio news in 1988.<br><br>Jeff dies and wakes up back in college in 1963, still remembering his life and knowing general important things about the world and used that to craft this replay of his life into one that he never could have dreamed of, with the goal of marrying the woman he loved again and being happy with her in a better life, and it works, they have a daughter, they didn't in his first life, he's content, he loves his family, he's rich, he lives a very happy life, and it's 1988 and he dies of a heart attack again. <br><br>Jeff wakes up in 1963 again. He remembers it all, his daughter is gone, everything gone. <br><br>Now the story really gets going. <br><br>This is a Plus book at the moment that expires on October 14, 2025 and I'm going to buy it, not right this second because I'm down to one credit, but I will buy it because I enjoyed the story so much after the second replay begins. <br><br>I also enjoy the narration by William Dufris who I've listened to on the Destroyermen series, and The Human Division, as well as some other works. <br><br>As I submit this there's still time to grab it on plus, 6 days, I hope others enjoy it as much as I did. </p>","title":"Way better than I expected"},{"asin":"B0FH5P5YK5","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> it's light and fun, same world as MM, and a nice snack while waiting for more Mistletoe. </p>","title":"if you like Mistletoe Mysteries, then you'll like this."},{"asin":"B0C8ZN3SV8","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> I honestly didn't expect much, but I was very surprised with how much I enjoyed this story. <br><br>It's a large departure from 616, and that's great. I think others will enjoy it and I will be getting the other one that's out with Spider-Man and the Scarlet Witch. </p>","title":"Very enjoyable"},{"asin":"B0CXF9PN9Q","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> A great little noir story. Flawed people, seedy folks, crime and justice.<br><br>Ed Harris really brought Dietrich to life. </p>","title":"Short and sweet"}];